  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6585.31 sitting just below the 6588 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will sell any push higher while buying dips aggressively. The massive +38.2B gamma wall at 6600 creates a strong ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the substantial positive gamma concentrations at 6580-6605 form a tight range that should contain price action. The detected wall break and GEX surge (32.5% 1-min change) suggests we just saw significant options flow that's now anchoring dealers to defend these levels more aggressively.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6580-6600 with dealers capping upside and supporting downside.",
